## Extracted Claims

### C001 | comparative

Emergency savings are positively associated with marital stability ($b = 0.029$, $SE = 0.009$, $p = .001$).

Evidence: Table tab:main_results -- Respondent fixed-effects LPM estimate b=0.029, SE=0.009, p=.001.

Boundary: Associational within-person estimate; not causal evidence that savings independently cause marital stability.

### C002 | descriptive

Financial literacy is not statistically associated with completed fertility in the Poisson model ($b = -0.010$, $SE = 0.008$, $p = .185$).

Evidence: Table tab:main_results -- Poisson estimate b=-0.010, SE=0.008, p=.185.

Boundary: Null result applies to constructed later-wave financial-literacy measure and primary model only.

### C003 | comparative

Adolescent exposure to birth-control education is associated with lower completed fertility ($b = -0.038$, $SE = 0.017$, $p = .026$) and later entry into parenthood ($HR = 0.930$, log-HR $SE = 0.024$, $p = .003$), although the timing estimate is interpreted cautiously because proportional-hazards diagnostics indicated possible assumption violation.

Evidence: Table tab:main_results -- Poisson estimate b=-0.038, SE=0.017, p=.026.

Boundary: Observational association; birth-control education exposure may proxy background, school, local norms, or access.

### C004 | descriptive

